You can generate a table of contents (TOC) automatically in a LaTeX document using the `\tableofcontents` command and the `\tocdepth` counter. Here's a complete example:

```latex
\documentclass{report}
\begin{document}

\tableofcontents

\setcounter{tocdepth}{2} % Generate TOC up to section and subsection levels

\section{Introduction}
\subsection{Background}
\subsubsection{History}

\section{Methods}
\subsection{Data Collection}
\subsubsection{Data Processing}

\section{Results}
\subsection{Main Findings}
\subsubsection{Analysis}

\end{document}
```

Let me explain what's happening:

1. `\documentclass{report}`: This selects the `report` document class, which includes support for a table of contents.
2. `\begin{document}`: This begins the document.
3. `\tableofcontents`: This command generates the table of contents. It will include all sections, subsections, and subsubsections (up to the level specified by `tocdepth`) from the document.
4. `\setcounter{tocdepth}{2}`: This sets the `tocdepth` counter to 2, which means the TOC will include sections and subsections, but not subsubsections. You can adjust this value to control the level of detail in the TOC.
5. The rest of the document contains the actual content, with section, subsection, and subsubsection headings.
6. `\end{document}`: This ends the document.

When you compile this LaTeX document, it will generate a table of contents that looks like this:

```
Contents
----------------

1 Introduction .................................................... 1
    1.1 Background ............................................... 1
    1.2 Subsection ............................................. 1
    1.2.1 Subsubsection ...................................... 1
2 Methods ....................................................... 2
    2.1 Data Collection ....................................... 2
    2.1.1 Data Processing .................................... 2
3 Results ....................................................... 3
    3.1 Main Findings ......................................... 3
    3.1.1 Analysis .......................................... 3

```

Note that the TOC entries are automatically generated based on the sectioning commands in your document. LaTeX takes care of formatting the TOC for you!

